title: Wanted driver climbs on car roof in Como chase | 7NEWS
description: A peak hour police pursuit in Como ended dramatically when a wanted driver climbed onto the roof of his red MG after being cornered by officers on Lockhart Street. The chase began in Bibra Lake and was tracked by police air wing through several suburbs, with the driver crossing to the wrong side of the road before the chaotic conclusion at 9:30am. A man in his 20s and a woman in her 30s were arrested following the incident. title: Man charged over $200k NDIS fraud scheme | 7NEWS
description: A Brookdale man has been arrested and charged with 160 offences following allegations he orchestrated an elaborate disability invoice scam that defrauded the National Disability Insurance Scheme of nearly $200,000. Police allege John Sutherland posed as a disability services coordinator, submitting fraudulent invoices while also engaging in identity theft, corporate account fraud, and luxury vehicle hire using false documents. The arrest occurred during a dramatic police chase that ended at a BP petrol station in Baldivis, with six people charged in total as part of the alleged criminal network. title: Prison conditions spark lighter sentences for violent criminals | 7NEWS
description: Western Australian judges are reducing prison sentences for violent criminals due to what they describe as inhumane conditions in Perth prisons, including cockroach infestations and extended lockdowns. A carjacker who attacked a 90-year-old grandfather received only two and a half years instead of a potential 20-year sentence, with the judge citing appalling conditions at Hakea prison as a contributing factor. WA prisons are operating at 98% capacity with 192 inmates sleeping on mattresses on the floor. title: Cloudflare outage grounds flights and crashes apps | 7NEWS
description: Cloudflare, a web security software company used by thousands of companies worldwide, suffered a network failure lasting several hours. The outage caused air traffic control systems to go down at airports in Melbourne, Adelaide and Perth, delaying flights and taking major apps like X, ChatGPT, Uber and Spotify offline. Cloudflare described the incident as an internal service degradation that they were working to fix. title: Two-way tolls proposed for Harbour Bridge | 7NEWS
description: Sydney drivers may face two-way tolls on the Harbour Bridge, with northbound traffic to be charged alongside the existing southbound toll. The Premier indicates this measure will help fund the $60 toll cap system that provides drivers with rebates of up to $340. The additional northbound toll will be implemented when the Western Harbour Tunnel opens. title: Parents launch methanol warning campaign after Laos tragedy | 7NEWS
description: The parents of Australian teenagers Holly Bowles and Bianca Jones, who died from methanol poisoning in Laos during their gap year, have launched a national campaign warning other schoolies about contaminated alcohol dangers.
